3. <antArtifact> Streaming Parser
Anthropic's artifact protocol embeds artifacts as XML-like tags inside the assistant's text content. They arrive piecewise across many content_block_delta { delta: { type: "text_delta", text: "..." } } events — the parser must accumulate without waiting for whole tags.

Tag forms
<antArtifact identifier="counter-app" type="application/vnd.ant.react" language="javascript" title="Counter App">
import React from 'react';
export default function App() { ... }
</antArtifact>

<antArtifact identifier="diagram-1" type="application/vnd.ant.mermaid" title="Flow">
graph TD; A-->B; B-->C;
</antArtifact>

<antArtifact identifier="report" type="text/markdown" title="Q3 Report">
# Q3 Report
...
</antArtifact>
Documented MIME types (Simon Willison's artifact archive3 cataloged the full set from claude.ai):

type	Renderer
application/vnd.ant.code	Monaco (read-only or editable)
application/vnd.ant.react	Sandboxed iframe with esbuild-wasm or Babel-standalone
